MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 364c2b772391e46dba637935c558b9b2, type: 3}
  m_Name: That_star_forged_blade_amark_of_warborne_plight
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::MythSO
  pageNumber: 57
  mythName: That star-forged blade amark of warborne plight
  omens:
  - '1. A booming voice singing in the distance. A

    travelling cook belts out
    songs about the

    Blade''s previous owners, each reaching a

    tragic end
    (see opposite).'
  - '2. A cliff-side village, ruined long enough to

    be overgrown with moss and
    thorns. In a

    ruined chapel an altar is inscribed with:

    Forsake in earth,
    unbroke by time

    Afore first draw, that greedsome war'
  - '3. Band of 5 cutthroats think the Knights

    have the Blade or know its whereabouts.'
  - '4. Down a spiral of natural steps, a bloodied

    sharpening wheel screams
    on the wind.

    Can sharpen blades to a keen edge (+d8)

    but they break
    after their first Wound.'
  - '5. A cave concealed by a steaming waterfall

    is the resting place of the
    Scabbard, which

    destroys any blade placed inside. The

    waterfall scalds
    (d10) anybody wielding a

    weapon, harmless to the unarmed.'
  - '6. A louse-infested dead forest. The Blade

    lies within, but travellers
    are lured by

    visions of something they truly desire.'
  verse: 'Omens

    1. A booming voice singing in the distance. A

    travelling
    cook belts out songs about the

    Blade''s previous owners, each reaching a

    tragic
    end (see opposite).

    2. A cliff-side village, ruined long enough to

    be
    overgrown with moss and thorns. In a

    ruined chapel an altar is inscribed
    with:

    Forsake in earth, unbroke by time

    Afore first draw, that greedsome
    war

    3. Band of 5 cutthroats think the Knights

    have the Blade or know
    its whereabouts.

    4. Down a spiral of natural steps, a bloodied

    sharpening
    wheel screams on the wind.

    Can sharpen blades to a keen edge (+d8)

    but
    they break after their first Wound.

    5. A cave concealed by a steaming waterfall

    is
    the resting place of the Scabbard, which

    destroys any blade placed inside.
    The

    waterfall scalds (d10) anybody wielding a

    weapon, harmless to the
    unarmed.

    6. A louse-infested dead forest. The Blade

    lies within, but
    travellers are lured by

    visions of something they truly desire.

    Cast

    The
    Blade, Sifrex, Ilglamvent

    2d8 hefty, wounded targets are utterly

    destroyed.
    The Blade''s wielder loses d6 SPI

    after each Attack.

    Cutthroats, Colan,
    Fia, Elga, Ness, Ruac

    VIG 10, CLA 10, SPI 7, 2 GD

    Longknife (d6), 2
    javelins (d6)

    Colan has a halfshield (d4, A1), angelic

    features, never
    sleeps, can Focus.

    He is truly bloodthirsty; the others less so.

    Granddad
    Louse, Rollyromple, Rockbug

    VIG 12, CLA 5, SPI 2, 5 GD

    A2, or A4 when
    rolled up (plated shell)

    Scuttering bite (2d6)

    Hungers for wooden items
    to hide in its lair

    and eat later. Fancy items appeal most.

    There it
    gleam''d as glore in meadow'' s sight'
  castEntries:
  - name: Cutthroats, Colan, Fia, Elga, Ness, Ruac
    statBlock: 'VIG 10, CLA 10, SPI 7, 2 GD

      Longknife (d6), 2 javelins (d6)'
    notes: 'Colan has a halfshield (d4, A1), angelic

      features, never sleeps,
      can Focus.

      He is truly bloodthirsty; the others less so.'
  - name: Granddad Louse, Rollyromple, Rockbug
    statBlock: 'VIG 12, CLA 5, SPI 2, 5 GD

      A2, or A4 when rolled up (plated
      shell)'
    notes: 'Scuttering bite (2d6)

      Hungers for wooden items to hide in its
      lair

      and eat later. Fancy items appeal most.

      There it gleam''d
      as glore in meadow'' s sight

      That star-forged blade amark of warborne
      plight

      PAST WIELDERS

      Name Tragic End

      1 Erdyg, Shamed Knight
      Throat cut

      2 Belwin, River Bandit Hanged from tree

      3 Gwelhelm,
      Butcher Poisoned feast

      4 Ordrig, Tower Guard Crushed by boulder

      5
      Regan, Cup Knight Lost underground

      6 Lervlin, Squire Drowned in river

      Blade

      Dwelling:
      Toll bridge ~ Sanctum: Tiny island ~ Monument: Guarded reliquary

      Hazard:
      Gulping marsh ~ Curse: Merciless winds ~ Ruin: Looted shrine

      Th'
  flavorTable:
    title: PAST WIELDERS
    rows:
    - 1 Erdyg, Shamed Knight Throat cut
    - 2 Belwin, River Bandit Hanged from tree
    - 3 Gwelhelm, Butcher Poisoned feast
    - 4 Ordrig, Tower Guard Crushed by boulder
    - 5 Regan, Cup Knight Lost underground
    - '6 Lervlin, Squire Drowned in river

      Blade'
  dwelling: Toll bridge
  sanctum: Tiny island
  monument: Guarded reliquary
  hazard: Gulping marsh
  curse: Merciless winds
  ruin: Looted shrine
  visibleByDefault: 0
  visibleMarkerPrefab: {fileID: 0}
